          <h2>About hackrLog()</h2>
          <p>
            I created <strong>hackrLog()</strong> for two reasons. Firstly, other note taking systems and methods
            didn't completely fit my needs. After trying wiki systems, online note apps, text files and plain
            paper notebooks I still didn't have a workable note taking system. I wanted something that would allow
            me to enter notes quickly without having to hunt down the correct wiki page or text file to enter the
            note into and also be able to find older notes just as quickly.
          </p>
          <p>
            Secondly, after reading <a href="http://pragprog.com/book/cfcar2/the-passionate-programmer" title="The Passionate Programmer">The Passionate Programmer</a>
            I wanted to keep a development log as mentioned in <strong>Tip 35. Me Rite Reel Nice</strong> as a way
            to improve my writing and to have a history of decisions regarding the projects I work on.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>hackrLog()</strong> is the note taking application I wanted for myself. I hope that other people
            will find it useful as well. Instead of hunting down the right wiki page or file to write a note you just
            write the note while it is fresh in your mind. Add tags to the note to categorize it and so that you can
            filter your stream of notes. See all of your notes from newest to oldest or turn on a filter for one or
            more tags to see only the notes you are interested in at the moment.
          </p>
