        <div id="philosophy" class="tab-pane fade">
          <h2>hackrLog() Philosophy</h2>
          <p>
            Some of the decisions I have made in developing this app may strike some people as strange, so I hope
            this section will explain a little about why things are the way they are.
          </p>
          <h3>Anti-Social?</h3>
          <p>
            You may notice there is no way to follow other members, no way to create public notes and no method for
            liking or rating notes. My desire was for this application to help developers with their work, not to be
            a popularity contest. When you join <strong>hackrLog()</strong> there is no pressure to build your network
            or increase your 'friend' count. Just write notes and find notes.
          </p>
          <h3>Why No Ad Supported Free Account?</h3>
          <p>
            This is pretty simple. I hate looking at ads. I'm sure most of you do too. You can rest easy knowing that
            all of your data is visible only to you. No advertiser will ever use it to target ads to you.
          </p>
